{#- §04 TIMELINE (the Desktop sunset — dated phases, 4-step) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="migration-timeline">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The Desktop sunset</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:20ch;margin-bottom:12px;">What&rsquo;s actually happening &mdash; and why timing matters.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 40px;max-width:62ch;">If you&rsquo;re still on QuickBooks Desktop, the question isn&rsquo;t whether to migrate &mdash; it&rsquo;s whether to do it on your schedule or during the industry rush. Enterprise customers are exempt from the sunset.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for t in timeline %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">{{ t.num | safe }}</div><h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ t.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §05 PHASES (the process — 4-step) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="migration-phases" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The process</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:16ch;margin-bottom:44px;">Every migration runs four phases.</h2>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in phases %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n{% if loop.last %} process-step__n--done{% endif %}">{{ s.num }} &middot; {{ s.when | safe }}{% if loop.last %} &check;{% endif %}</div><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §06 MIGRATION INTEGRITY PROTOCOL (coined term — 7-point checklist) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="migration-integrity">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The Migration Integrity Protocol</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:22ch;margin-bottom:12px;">Seven things verified before any migration is signed off.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:60ch;">The free Intuit tool moves data. The <strong>Migration Integrity Protocol</strong> is how we prove the moved file is actually correct &mdash; seven checks run against the source before handoff.</p>
    <div class="incl-card">
      <h3>The Migration Integrity Protocol &mdash; 7-point verification</h3>
      <ul class="checklist">
        {%- for d in integrity %}<li><strong>{{ d.point | safe }}.</strong> {{ d.body | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §07 DELIVERABLES (included + scope-layered checklists) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="migration-deliverables" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The deliverables</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:20ch;margin-bottom:36px;">What you actually get from a migration engagement.</h2>
    <div class="r-2" style="gap:24px;">
      <div class="incl-card">
        <h3>Every migration includes</h3>
        <ul class="checklist">{%- for d in included %}<li>{{ d | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
      </div>
      <div class="incl-card">
        <h3>Handled when scope requires</h3>
        <ul class="checklist">{%- for d in configured %}<li>{{ d | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §08 HONEST-TRIAGE (Intuit free tool — Sheet-7 disclosure, .cmp compare, verbatim) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="migration-tool">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx idx--center"><span class="idx__rule"></span><span class="idx__t">Honest about Intuit&rsquo;s free tool</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <div class="read" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2 class="statement">What Intuit&rsquo;s migration tool does &mdash; and doesn&rsquo;t do.</h2>
      <p class="lede" style="margin:0 auto 8px;max-width:62ch;">Intuit&rsquo;s free tool is real and it works for the technical data transfer. It&rsquo;s what it <em>doesn&rsquo;t</em> do that produces unusable files.</p>
    </div>
    <table class="cmp" data-viz="comparison-table" data-viz-state="FINAL" style="margin-top:40px;">
      <caption class="sr-only">Professional migration versus Intuit&rsquo;s free migration tool, by capability.</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Capability</th><th scope="col" class="us">Professional migration</th><th scope="col">Intuit free tool</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for row in toolCompare %}
        <tr><th scope="row">{{ row.dim | safe }}</th><td class="us" data-col="Professional migration"><strong>{{ row.us | safe }}</strong></td><td data-col="Intuit free tool">{{ row.other | safe }}</td></tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §09 MODERNIZATION (statement + prose — what migration is actually for) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="migration-modernization">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What migration is actually for</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:24px;">Migration is the modernization. The capabilities are what matter.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Migration as a forced reaction to Intuit&rsquo;s sunset roadmap is the wrong way to think about the move. Migration as deliberate modernization &mdash; positioning the business for the next decade of accounting work &mdash; is the right way.</p>
      <p>A well-migrated QuickBooks Online file enables what Desktop couldn&rsquo;t: cloud accessibility for distributed teams, real-time CPA collaboration instead of file-handoff cycles, modern integrations with payment processors and e-commerce and time-tracking tools, better lender and investor positioning for capital events, and the foundation for advisory work &mdash; cash-flow forecasting, scenario planning, margin analysis &mdash; that requires data your CPA can actually access.</p>
      <p>Most TechBrot migration engagements transition into monthly bookkeeping with the same operator, and many continue further as the business grows. The migration is the modernization moment. Done right, it unlocks the next decade.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
